The paper deals with graph property testing, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The bounded-degree graph model is a common model in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the concept of hyperfiniteness, which is related to the study of graph structure and connectivity (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the distribution of $k$-disks on subsets of a partition class.
